<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 16 at 2:41PM EDT  by NWS Grand Rapids</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Gratiot, Isabella,
Clare, Osceola, Mecosta and northeastern Montcalm Counties through
345 PM EDT...
At 241 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Big Rapids to near Carson City. Movement was
northeast at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Mount Pleasant...      Big Rapids...          Alma...
Clare...               Ithaca...              Evart...
St. Louis...           Reed City...           Shepherd...
Breckenridge...        Edmore...              Marion...
Farwell...             Mecosta...             Rosebush...
Lake Isabella...       Harrison...            Canadian Lakes...
Wheeler...             Crystal...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
